An 81-year-old man was killed in a massive fire that ravaged his Long Island home Wednesday evening, authorities said. Earl Rahman was found dead inside the home on Magnolia Drive near Talbot Lane in Selden, where firefighters battled a blaze that erupted there around 6:20 p.m., Suffolk County Police said. Shocking footage shows the home completely enveloped in raging flames as firefighters converge on the scene. No other injuries were reported. A preliminary investigation reveals that the fire was non-criminal in nature, police said.